                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Tower</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 11, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Tower reports that Department’s telegram, announcing that instructions have
                    been sent to the United States representatives at St. Petersburg, Tokyo, and
                    Peking, has been communicated to the German minister for foreign affairs, and he
                    replied that the necessary instructions will be sent at once to the German
                    representatives in those capitals. He was also informed that the views of the
                    United States will be communicated immediately to all the neutral signatories of
                    the protocol of Peking.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
